x4freetext: Distorted-wave Born-approximation
analysis was used to interpret the reaction results.
Single-particle strength distributions have been
studied.
The over-all uncertainty in absolute reaction
cross sections is estimated to be about 25%.
Relative uncertainties for measurements
at different angles are given by the counting
statistics which were between 3 and 10%
OG
Reaction products were detected in nuclear
emulsions by using an Enge broad-range spectrograph.
Line targets of 43Ca 1 mm in width were prepared by
simultaneous decomposition of CaCO3 and evaporation
of the Ca as metal from a tantalum boat. Targets were
evaporated on carbon foils 20 mu-g/cm2 in thickness.
Target thickness was about 60 mu-g/cm2.
The statistical error is indicated by error
bars in the figure only when the error exceeds the size
of the circles.
